ited)\n*1955 ''[[Interrupted Melody]]'' (uncredited)\n*1956 ''[[Tea and Sympathy (film)|Tea and Sympathy]]''\n*1956 ''[[The Rack (1956 film)|The Rack]]''\n*1958 ''[[The Matchmaker (1958 film)|The Matchmaker]]''\n*1959 ''[[Some Like It Hot]]'' (background score)\n*1960 ''[[The Apartment]]''\n*1961 ''[[Go Naked in the World]]'' \n                              \n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0006037|Adolph Deutsch}}\n*https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/87586/Adolph-Deutsch at the New York Times\n*http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/c2a3945a-6b41-496f-8072-7efe10a5c561 at the BBC\n\n{{AcademyAwardBestOriginalScore 1941-1960}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deutsch, Adolph}}\n[[Category:1897 births]]\n[[Category:1980 deaths]]\n[[Category:Best Original Music Score Academy Award winners]]\n[[Category:English conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:British male conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:English film score composers]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from London]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Buffalo, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Palm Desert, California]]\n[[Category:20th-century conductors (music)]]\n[[Category:20th-century British composers]]\n[[Category:20th-century English musicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male musicians]]\n", "name_user": "Tassedethe", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - Repaired 1 link to disambiguation page -(You can help)-Flowing Gold", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolph_Deutsch"}
{"title_page": "Lucy Fox", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name         =   Lucy Fox\n| image         = File:Lucy Fox - Sep 1921 Photoplay.jpg\n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = Fox in ''Photoplay'', September 1921\n| birth_date   = October 25, 1897 \n| birth_place  = [[New York, New York]], [[United States]]\n| death_date   = May 21, 1970\n| death_place =  [[Palm Beach, Florida]], United States\n| othername   =  \n| occupation  =  Actress\n| yearsactive = 1918-1925 (film)\n}}\n'''Lucy Fox''' (1897\u20131970) was an American actress active in the era of [[silent film]].<ref>Solomon, p. 290</ref>\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Just for Tonight (film)|Just for Tonight]]'' (1918)\n* ''[[Why I Would Not Marry?]]'' (1918)\n* ''[[The Bishop's Emeralds]]'' (1919)\n* ''[[The Winchester Woman]]'' (1919)\n* ''[[Something Different (1920 film)|Something Different]]'' (1920)\n* ''[[Hurricane Hutch]]'' (1921)\n* ''[[The Money Maniac]]'' (1921)\n* ''[[My Old Kentucky Home (1922 film)|My Old Kentucky Home]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Sonny (1922 film)|Sonny]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Speed (serial)|Speed]]'' (1922)\n* ''[[Teeth (1924 film)|Teeth]]'' (1924)\n* ''[[The Trail Rider]]'' (1925)\n* ''[[The Arizona Romeo]]'' (1925)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Solomon, Aubrey. ''The Fox Film Corporation, 1915-1935: A History and Filmography''. McFarland, 2011.\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0289127}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fox, Lucy}}\n[[Category:1897 births]]\n[[Category:1970 deaths]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:People from New York City]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n\n\n{{US-film-actor-1890s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name         =   Lucy Fox\n| image         = File:Lucy Fox - Sep 1921 Photoplay.jpg\n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = Fox in ''Photoplay'', September 1921\n| birth_date   = October 25, 1897 \n| birth_place  = [[New York, New York]], [[United States]]\n| death_date   = Ma